e feed-forward and cortical frequency representations is eliminated. We therefore predict that cortico-geniculate feedback connections innervate the {LGN} in a pattern determined by the orientation and spatial-frequency biases of feed-forward receptive fields. Finally, we show how recurrent cortical interactions can generate cross-orientation suppression.},
