nd duration of 6.2 +/- 0.3 ({SE}) ms and 61.2 +/- 2.0 ms, respectively, and an amplitude of approximately 1 {mV} (n = 93). The {AP}5-sensitive component of {EPSPs} was only detected when the cell was depolarized with respect to the resting potential, had a mean time-to-peak of 41 +/- 5 ms and duration of 121 +/- 11 ms (n = 6), and increased in amplitude with postsynaptic depolarization. 6. Unitary monosynaptic {IPSPs} between an interneuron and a pyramidal cell had a mean amplitude of approximately 1 {mV} and were fully blocked by gamma-aminobutyric acid-A ({GABAA}) receptor antagonists (n = 3). 7. Unitary inhibitory responses were found only within, but not between, areas {CA}3 or {CA}1.({ABSTRACT} {TRUNCATED} {AT} 400 {WORDS})},
